<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF110-427-004  </DOCNO><DOCID>10 427 004.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Communications  Dec 1990 v13 n10 p619(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Monitoring tool for the Cambridge Ring LAN. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fulcher, John; McKerrow, Phillip.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A Cambridge Ring monitor station can detect breaks in a LAN, aswell as pinpoint nodes which are causing data corruption.andO;However, no facility exists for inspecting the data actually beingtransmitted by a corrupting node.andP;  A design for a Cambridge Ringprobe is described which enables such data capture.andP;  Moreover,this probe can be used in conjunction with an oscilloscope forlow-level fault finding, or together with a logic state analyserfor high-level fault finding and/or performance measurement.andO;Preliminary results are presented which demonstrate the usefulnessof the probe for the former.andP;  A discussion of how the probe can beused for the latter is also included.andP;  (Reprinted by permission ofthe publisher.)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Local Area NetworksData Capture DevicesFault TolerancePerformance MeasurementData Collection.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Physical structure of the Cambridge Ring LAN. (chart)Data encoding. (chart)Packet structure. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>